item.p:
to amend the Plant Health (Scotland) Order 2005 (“the 2005 Order”), in order to expressly transpose certain obligations of the member State contained in Council Directive 93/85/EEC
                     on the control of potato ring rot (OJ L 259, 18.10.1993, p.1), Council Directive 98/57/EC on the control of Ralstonia
                     solanacearum (Smith) Yabuuchi et al (OJ L. 235, 21.8.1998, p.1) and Council Directive 2007/33/EC on the control of potato cyst nematodes and repealing Directive 69/465/EEC (OJ L 156, 16.6.2007, p.12) to ensure that those provisions become “retained EU law” at exit day, for the purposes of the 2018 Act;
